Building SheepShaver for Lion:

- Dependencies
	- SDL framework
		- Download SDL.framework from http://libsdl.org , put it in
		  /Library/Frameworks
	- automake and autoconf
		- Installable from MacPorts
	- Apple's GCC 4.2 (non-LLVM)
		- Get it from XCode 3 OR install apple-gcc42 from MacPorts
	- A modern GCC
		- install gcc47 from MacPorts

- Configuring
	- Generate configure files
		$ NO_CONFIGURE=1 ./autogen.sh
	- Set PIE (Position Independent Executables) off
		- This is critically important, do not forget!
		$ export MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET=10.6
	- Configure, with GCC 4.2
		$ CC=gcc-4.2 CXX=g++-4.2 ./configure --enable-sdl-video \
		  --enable-sdl-audio --enable-sdl-framework --disable-vosf --enable-jit

- Building
	- Build `dyngen` with a modern GCC
		$ make obj &&  make DYNGEN_CC=g++-mp-4.7 dyngen
	- Build everything else with Apple's GCC
		$ make -j2
	- Build the .app, ignoring GNU find
		$ PATH=/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/sbin make SheepShaver_app
	- If you want, build SheepShaverLauncher in src/MacOSX
		- Use my launcher-xcode46 branch
